# Macro thesis
*Living document. Last updated: April 2026. Source: three years of investment memos (Aug 2023, late 2024, Dec 2025) refined into a working framework.*

---

## Investment philosophy — first principles

Macro conditions first, then factor filtering, then bottom-up fundamentals. Not a pure top-down macro trader — the macro view narrows the universe; position selection still requires fundamental justification.

Preferred style: **value and quality, with GARP tolerance**. Willing to pay for quality if the business compounds. Not willing to pay for narrative.

Factor tilt hierarchy (current cycle): **value > quality > size > momentum (neutral) > low beta (short)**. Willing to stay long volatility given the time horizon. No leverage. No uncovered options.

Benchmark tolerance: 0.9–1.2 beta vs S&P 500. Active sleeve capped at 7.5% target / 10% soft ceiling of household AUM.

Retail edge framework: time horizon (hold through institutional career-risk forcing functions), no risk committee (can take positions institutional capital structurally cannot), tax alpha (TLH, asset location, long-term gain management).

